results.occurrenceRemarks: What a beautiful beetle! Amazing in flight with the two halves of its colourful shell cocked upwards like doors on a gull-winged car. Apparently this was one of the species collected on the first Cook voyage to New Zealand, and described by Fabricius in 1775 (one of the first scientifically described insects for New Zealand).
